
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `lzless` mesle `less` ast, amma baraye file-haye `gzip` ya `lzma` shode be kar miravad. Yani, file-haye ziad bozorg ra ke ziad shode-and, bedoon baz kardane aanha, mitavanid bebinid.  

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `lzless +F`  --> 👀 Age file tagheer konad, `lzless` automatic update mishavad.
    🔹 `lzless -N`  --> 🔢 Raftare `less` ra ba file-haye gheyre-ziad shode control mikonad.
    🔹 `lzless -o file`  --> 💾 Output ra dar yek file save mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ lzless myfile.gz

    🔹 Didane file `gzip` shode `myfile.gz`.

    $ lzless bigfile.lzma

    🔹 Didane file `lzma` shode `bigfile.lzma`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ lzless logfile.gz | grep error

    🔹 File ziad shode `logfile.gz` ra mibinad va khat-hayi ke `error` darand ra neshan midahad. In kar kheili sari az baz kardane file va grep kardan ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `lzless` command is similar to `less`, but designed to work with `gzip` or `lzma` compressed files. This allows you to view large compressed files without needing to decompress them first.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `lzless +F`  --> 👀 Follow mode; `lzless` will automatically update if the file changes.
    🔹 `lzless -N`  --> 🔢 Controls how `less` behaves when the input file isn't compressed.
    🔹 `lzless -o file`  --> 💾 Saves the output to a specified file.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ lzless myfile.gz

    🔹 View the `gzip` compressed file `myfile.gz`.

    $ lzless bigfile.lzma

    🔹 View the `lzma` compressed file `bigfile.lzma`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ lzless logfile.gz | grep error

    🔹 Views the compressed `logfile.gz` and filters for lines containing `error`.  This is much faster than decompressing and then grepping the file.
